<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-23yOcwuVTy1bJcWTnxl7rw" name=",_kqHwgL-dEd2e1-cAeXIm5A" guid="-23yOcwuVTy1bJcWTnxl7rw" changeDate="2008-12-01T12:46:01.984+0100">
  <mainDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=ES-TRAD style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;>This task is the final effort to select the definitive architecture of the composition. Some architecture alternatives were identified previously, but some necessary abstract services have been identified and the context might have changed, so it is necessary to analyse if the best alternative remains the same. &lt;/SPAN>&lt;SPAN style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US&quot;>The result of this task will be a Business Process Skeleton which can be expressed as a UML component or class diagram, showing graphically the structural organization of the services at runtime. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/P></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_UBdqEcHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw" name="Analyse validity of the alternatives identified before " guid="_UBdqEcHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=ES-TRAD style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>First, analyse all the information gathered before this process. This implies to take architecture recommendations from Architectural options &amp;amp; policies and abstract service descriptions from SSM. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=ES-TRAD style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>The objective is to extract which architectural options will not be valid due to the services identified or the new context.&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;>&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN>Usually, architecture options will not be modified and the most important job will be to check if all the architectures, using proposed services, are feasible or have to be modified. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_UBdqE8HrEd2B2LAvnwDruw" name="Do some changes in those architectures which need them " guid="_UBdqE8HrEd2B2LAvnwDruw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=ES-TRAD style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>If there is any architecture which became not feasible, try to do little modifications in such a way it will be feasible again with the available abstract services. The architecture can be affected by changes in some requirements. Try to analyse those changes to understand how to evolve architectures and obtain new alternatives closer to the user requirements. If data about similar problems in other projects is available, try to apply those solutions which were useful.&lt;SPAN style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes&quot;>&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN>&lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=ES-TRAD style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Changes in abstract service descriptions could also be proposed to improve composition performance or to maintain architecture feasibility in those cases where there are problems with the abstract services identified. &lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_UBdqEsHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw" name="Select the architecture to be used in the composition " guid="_UBdqEsHrEd2B2LAvnwDruw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=ES-TRAD style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt&quot;>&lt;FONT face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;>Finally, update architecture ranking and evaluate which is the best architecture to be used as the skeleton of the composition. Indicate whether the architecture might be modified to obtain better results or should remain as is. &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = &quot;urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office&quot; />&lt;o:p>&lt;/o:p>&lt;/FONT>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&lt;SPAN lang=ES-TRAD style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: ES-TRAD; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>It is recommended to use a knowledge base (when available) to contrast obtained solution with previous solutions. This action could help to improve both the knowledge base (attaching learnt lessons) and the proposed solution (applying known and tested improvements).&lt;/SPAN></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;span lang=&quot;ES-TRAD&quot;&#xD;
style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: ES-TRAD; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>This&#xD;
task is the final effort to select the definitive architecture of the composition&lt;/span></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
